# Architecture Map

| Package | Responsibility |
|---------|----------------|
| `maze/game` | `Maze` orchestrator, `Launcher`, `MazeEvent`, `GameTime`, `GameState`, `game/event/` |
| `maze/map` | `Zone`, `Tile`, `Portal`, `TileScript` (world model); `map/crusader/` bridges to the raycaster |
| `maze/stat` | Rules + model: actors, items, `combat/`, `magic/`, `condition/`, `npc/` |
| `maze/ui/diygui` | Game screens; `MazeWidget` blits the raycaster image |
| `maze/data` | `Database` facade, `Loader`/`Saver`, V2 JSON serialisers |
| `maze/editor/swing` | Swing content editor |
| `crusader` | Raycaster engine (no game knowledge) |
| `diygui` | Widget toolkit (no game knowledge) |

## Event-thread rule (important)

All game-state changes happen on the single event thread as `MazeEvent`s. From UI
/ AWT code, enqueue events instead of mutating state directly:

```java
// Prefer
Maze.getInstance().appendEvents(new MovePartyEvent(...));

// Avoid: mutating party/zone/combat state directly from a widget/listener
```

`MazeEvent.resolve()` returns child events processed depth-first. Reusable
sequences are `MazeScript`s (data in `scripts.json`).

## Dual map model

A `Zone` holds both a Crusader `Map` (render geometry) and a `Tile[][]` (game
logic). Changes that affect geometry and logic must update both consistently.

## Swappable implementations

`UserInterface`, `GameSys`, `MagicSys`, `Loader`/`Saver`, and the GUI
`RendererFactory` are selected reflectively from `maze.cfg`. Prefer extending via
these strategy points over hard-coding.
